definition.value: An alicyclic primary alcohol that is cyclohexane substituted by a hydroxy methyl group and methyl group at positions 1 and 4. It acts as a hydrotrope, solubilizing hydrophobic substances in aqueous environments. It also prevents protein aggregation, alters membrane dynamics and metal homeostasis, and is used in a flotation process for cleaning and processing coal.
A dicarboxylic acid dianion resuting from deprotonation of both carboxy groups of 3-oxoadipic acid.
A carbohydrate acid derivative anion that is a polyanionic form of heparan sulfate arising from global deprotonation of the carboxy and N-sulfo groups; major species at pH 7.3.
A dioxo monocarboxylic acid anion that is the conjugate base of 4-(2-amino-3-hydroxyphenyl)-2,4-dioxobutanoic acid resulting from the deprotonation of the carboxy group. Major species at pH 7.3.
An anionic phospholipid obtained by deprotonation of the carboxy and phosphate groups of 1,2-diacyl-sn-glycero-3-phospho-(N-acyl)-L-serine; major species at pH 7.3.
An anionic lysophospholipid obtained by deprotonation of the carboxy and phosphate groups of 1-acyl-2-hydroxy-sn-glycero-3-phospho-(N-acyl)-L-serine; major species at pH 7.3.
Any glycosylmonoglyceride in which the glycosyl moiety is attached to one of the primary hydroxy groups and the acyl group position is not defined.
A cephalosporin antibiotic carrying a 3-acetoxymethyl substituent and a 6-oxo-N(6)-L-lysino group at position 7.
An anionic phospholipid obtained by deprotonation of the phospho groups of any glycerophosphoethanol; major species at pH 7.3.
A guanosine 5'-phosphate that is 7-methyl-GTP(1+) in which the hydroxy group of the terminal phosphate is substituted by an adenosyl group. It is a cap analog that can be incorporated into mRNA.
A polyprenol phosphate in which the hydroxyl hydrogen is replaced by a phospho group, major species at pH 7.3.
A class of saccharolipids.
A fatty acyl-CoA that is hydroxylated at position 2 of the acyl chain, major species at pH 7.3.
Any primary fatty alcohol with a chain length less than 6 carbons.
A docosanoid anion arising from deprotonation of the carboxylic acid function of any hydroperoxydocosapentaenoic acid.
A docosanoid anion arising from deprotonation of the carboxylic acid function of any epoxydocosatetraenoic acid.
A docosanoid anion arising from deprotonation of the carboxylic acid function of any epoxydocosapentaenoic acid.
A docosanoid anion arising from deprotonation of the carboxylic acid function of any epoxydocosahexaenoic acid.
The chloramide form of CHEBI:55424
The chloramide form of CHEBI:55478
Any N-acyl-amino acid in which the amino acid moiety has D configuration.
The organic sodium salt of sulbactam.
A dipeptide obtained by formal condensation of the carboxy group of L-alanine with the amino group of L-cysteine.
